    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sun-dried-tomato-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sun-dried-tomato-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen<strong> </strong>paper</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sun-dried-tomato-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the lardons are golden, add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and cook for 2 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sun-dried-tomato-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>quick cook spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>spaghetti</strong> for 2-3 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>spaghetti</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sun-dried-tomato-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have softened, reduce the heat to medium-high and add your<strong> balsamic sun-dried tomato paste</strong> and<strong> finely chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pan with your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further or until thickened</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> bacon & sun-dried tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sun-dried-tomato-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> to the bacon & sun-dried tomato sauce and give everything a good mix up until the pasta is fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>bacon & sun-dried tomato spaghetti</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-sun-dried-tomato-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bacon & sun-dried tomato spaghetti</strong> topped with the <strong>salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>salad</strong> with a little <strong>olive oil</strong> and sprinkle your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
